AB  - Beyond the Westphalian rainbow: a dissident theory of supranational systems. Territory, Politics, Governance. This article focuses on the work of Adam Watson from the English School of International Relations for two purposes. The first is to highlight the potential it contains for transcending the prejudices imposed upon international relations theory by the anarchy assumption and by the reification of independent statehood. The second and the more specific purpose is to understand the formation of legitimate supranational systems once these prejudices are removed. Watson approaches supranationalism as an extant condition in international society rather than as a deviation from a normal condition of anarchy or independent statehood, and proposes a culturalist and a moralistic framework in which supranational systems can be legitimized. As a case study to determine which framework is more valid, I analysed the convention on the future of Europe and concluded that the moralistic serves better for understanding how the European Union is legitimized. Once juxtaposed with Neo-Weberian historical sociology’s insights into the state, Watson’s moralistic framework can offer a foundational theory for reconsidering legitimate supranational systems and open up new research agendas in international relations theory.Alternate abstract:摘要西伐利亚的国家集锦之外：超国家系统的异议理论。 Territory, Politics, Governance. 本文为了下述两造目的，聚焦来自国际关係英国学派的亚当．华生之着作：第一个目的在于强调它超越无政府预设和独立国家状态的具体化所施加在国际关係理论上的偏见之潜能。第二个更为具体的目的，在于理解上述偏见移除后，合法的超国家系统的形成。华生将超国家主义视为国际社会中的现行状态，而非无政府或独立国家状态的常规境况之外的偏差，并提出文化主义与道德主义的架构，其中超国家系统能够被合法化。我分析了欧盟未来制宪大会，作为証实何种架构更为有效的案例研究，并以道德架构能够更佳理解欧盟如何合法化的主张作结。当与新韦伯式历史社会学对国家的洞见并陈时，华生的道德架构能够提供重新思考合法的超国家系统之基础理论，并在国际关係理论中开啓崭新的研究议程。
